The course gives an overview of the anthropogenesis, the material culture and societies of the early hominids, the colonization of America and Australia, the period of Late Palaeolithic in Europe and Asia, the material cultures and societies of the Mesolithic in Europe and Asia, the beginning of the agriculture in different places of the world, the spreading of cultivation and cattle-breeding and the Neolithic societies in Europe.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the course is to provide an outline of the oldest period of the prehistory of mankind - the Stone Age - starting with early hominids until the first societies using metal tools.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  The student who has passed the course has an overviw of the cultural, technological and social processes that took place during the Stone Age and knows the main topics of this period.
